IoT QBS Service Remediation API Specification
Overview
The IoT QBS Service Remediation API provides REST endpoints for reading order/service data, retrieving OE and Configuration attributes from CloudSense managed packages, patching incorrect service-to-PC mappings, and releasing orchestration holds. These APIs are consumed exclusively by BSS Magic as part of the IoT QBS remediation workflow.

All APIs are a thin data layer -- they perform data access only (SOQL reads, managed package callouts, DML writes). All business logic (validation, SIM-to-PC mapping, patch payload construction, decisioning) resides in BSS Magic.

Base Path: /services/apexrest/api/v1/iot-qbs-orders

Authentication
All API requests require Salesforce OAuth 2.0:



Authorization: Bearer {access_token}
Base URL
Production: https://{instance}.salesforce.com/services/apexrest/api/v1/iot-qbs-orders

Sandbox: https://{sandbox-instance}.salesforce.com/services/apexrest/api/v1/iot-qbs-orders

