Per-PC design rationale: Each Apex REST call is a separate Salesforce transaction with its own governor limits (100 SOQL, 150 DML, 100 callouts). API 2 and API 3 are called once per PC so each call gets a fresh governor budget.

When to Use Each Endpoint
API 1 (GET): Call first. Returns lightweight discovery data -- PCs metadata and service summaries. BSS Magic uses PCs metadata (especially guid and solutionId) to call API 2, and service summaries to later compare SIMs against the truth table. Read-only, safe to retry.

API 2 (GET /pc-data/{pcId}): Call after API 1, once per PC. Returns OE attributes (per service line -- provides ICCID truth table for SIM-to-PC mapping) and Configuration attributes (per PC -- provides PriceItemId/Plan only available here). Read-only, safe to retry. Pass guid and solutionId as query parameters.

API 3 (PUT /services): Call only after BSS Magic has completed validation and built the patch payload. Only mismatched services included. BSS Magic groups by target PC and calls once per PC. The API trusts the payload entirely -- no server-side validation.

API 4 (POST /release): Call only after successful revalidation confirms all mappings are correct. If the orchestration is already released, returns 200 with "already_released": true (safe to retry).

