oeData

Array

OE components from getOEData. Each component contains configurations, each configuration contains attributes (name/value/displayValue). One set of attributes per service line (per SIM/ICCID within this PC).

configData

Object

Configuration attributes from getConfigurations. One set per PC. Contains attributes only available here: PriceItemId, Plan.

Internal Implementation (Zero SOQL)
The wrapper performs no SOQL queries. All identifiers are provided via path and query parameters (from API 1 response).

Calls cssmgnt.API_1.getOEData(new List<Id>{pcId}) -- returns Map<Id, List<cssmgnt.ProductProcessingUtility.Component>>

Calls new cssmgnt.api_1().getConfigurations(solutionId, new List<String>{guid}) -- returns JSON string

Combines into response

Serialization constraint (verified in maxisfdrv2 org): JSON.serialize() throws System.JSONException: Cannot serialize type from package: cssmgnt.ProductProcessingUtility.Component. The wrapper must manually iterate Component -> Configuration -> Attribute and build plain Map<String, Object> structures:



Component -> name (String, can be null)
          -> configurations (List)
              -> Configuration -> attributes (List)
                                  -> Attribute -> name (String)
                                              -> value (String)
                                              -> displayValue (String)
The getConfigurations response is a native JSON string and has no serialization issue.

Governor impact: 0 SOQL, 0 DML, 2 callouts (getOEData + getConfigurations).

