3. Patch Services
Updates service records with corrected field values. BSS Magic groups mismatched services by their target (correct) PC and calls this endpoint once per PC. This bounds DML rows per transaction.

Endpoint: PUT /iot-qbs-orders/{orchestrationProcessId}/services

Request
Headers:



Authorization: Bearer {access_token}
Content-Type: application/json
Path Parameters:

Parameter

Type

Required

Description

orchestrationProcessId

String

Yes

Orchestration Process ID

Request Body:

BSS Magic sends SFDC field API names directly in the fields map. The API performs no field-name mapping and no whitelist validation -- it applies the values via svc.put(fieldName, value) and executes DML. If BSS Magic sends a field name that does not exist on csord__Service__c, Apex throws SObjectException which is caught and returned as a structured 500 error. Access control is enforced at the platform level (Connected App + Permission Set), not in the API code.

This means extending the set of patchable fields requires only a BSS Magic code change -- zero Salesforce deployment.



{
  "services": [
    {
      "serviceId": "a1Sxx00000SVC001",
      "fields": {
