Integration Flow
Step-by-step BSS Magic workflow calling APIs in sequence:

BSS Magic detects a held orchestration (via polling or webhook -- not via these APIs).

API 1: GET /iot-qbs-orders/{orchestrationProcessId} -- receives PCs metadata and service summaries.

API 2 (loop): For each PC from step 2, call GET /iot-qbs-orders/{id}/pc-data/{pcId}?guid=X&solutionId=Y -- receives OE + Config data for that PC.

BSS Magic builds truth table, validates, constructs patch payload (all internal logic).

API 3 (loop): For each PC with mismatches, call PUT /iot-qbs-orders/{id}/services with services grouped by target PC.

API 1 (revalidation): GET /iot-qbs-orders/{orchestrationProcessId} -- reload to confirm all correct.

API 4: POST /iot-qbs-orders/{id}/release -- release the hold.